article.description: — Johnathan Massie's 20 points helped Longwood defeat Lamar 83-72 on Saturday.
article.headline: Longwood defeats Lamar 83-72
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- — Johnathan Massie's 20 points helped Longwood defeat Lamar 83-72 on Saturday. Massie had eight rebounds for the Lancers (5-1). Michael Christmas and Elijah Tucker each scored 12 points. The Cardinals (3-3) were led in scoring by BB Knight, who finished with 21 points. Jakevion Buckley added 13 points and four assists for Lamar. In addition, Cody Pennebaker finished with nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
